ct is strncpy_from_user() copying extra garbage after NUL byte.<br /><br />BPF made the wrong expectation.<br /><br />Those bytes are not defined, and it's faster the way it is written.<br /><br />Nobody else cares.<br /><br />BPF needs to fix it's usage. It really is that simple.<br /><br />strncpy_from_user() is one of the hottest functions in the whole<br />kernel (under certain not very uncommon loads), and it's been<br />optimized for performance.<br /><br />You told it that the destination buffer was some amount of bytes, and<br />strncpy_from_user() will use up to that maximum number of bytes.<br />That's the only guarantee you have - it won't write _past_ the buffer<br />you gave it.<br /><br />The fact that you then use the string not as a string, but as<br />something else, that's why *you* need to change your code.<br /><br />            Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
